[3] New Jersey (Newark): airport
Date: Sat 29 Dec 2018
Source: Fox News [abridged, edited]
https://www.foxnews.com/health/international-traveler-with-measles-arrived-at-new-jersey-airport-state-health-officials-say-warn-of-possible-exposure


An individual who flew to a New Jersey airport on Christmas Eve has a confirmed case of the measles, health officials said Friday [28 Dec 2018], warning that others could have been exposed.

The traveler with the "highly contagious disease" flew into Newark Liberty International Airport's Terminal B on 24 Dec 2018 from Brussels, the New Jersey Department of Health revealed in a news release. The infected person was contagious at the time and possibly went to other parts of the travel hub, officials said.

"New Jersey residents identified as potentially exposed on the ill individual's flights will be notified by their local health department," health officials said.

This instance has no connection to an outbreak of the disease elsewhere in the state; cases have shown up in Ocean and Passaic counties. Health commissioner Dr. Shereef Elnahal urged people to receive vaccinations.

The notice about the measles-infected traveler was also posted on Twitter by the New Jersey Department of Health.

