[4] Madagascar
Date: Fri 28 Dec 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/madagascar-measles-outbreak-grows-23-of-cases-from-analamanga-region-92244/


Madagascar measles outbreak grows, 2/3 of cases from Analamanga region. Total cases rise to 15 049 since 1 Oct 2018
----------------

In a follow-up on the measles outbreak in Madagascar, local media reports the outbreak case total has risen to 15 049 cases since 1 Oct 2018. About 65% of these cases were reported in the Analamanga region. During the last 3 months, 48 districts in Madagascar were affected by the measles epidemic, 6 of which recorded more than 400 cases.

The district of Antananarivo Renivohitra has the highest number of cases with 8869 patients, followed by that of Ambato Boeny with 947 cases, Marovoay with 693 cases, Mahajanga I with 518 cases, Ambohidratrimo with 466 cases, and Antananarivo Atsimondrano with 412 cases.

How contagious is measles? Answer: very.

--
