[On this last day of 2018, we see the greatest number of measles cases in Europe in 8 years: more than 41 000 children and adults were infected with measles in the 1st 6 months of 2018. The predominant number of cases were reported from Romania, France, Greece, and Italy. Even in countries with a high level of immunization such as Ireland, as discussed in this report, travel-associated cases occur and start an outbreak. The level of immunity needed to be maintained in the population is 95%, or possibly higher since a certain proportion of the population is too young to be vaccinated or cannot for medical reasons. Vaccine hesitancy is a serious problem, as is movement of unvaccinated peoples fleeing their country of origin where vaccination has been allowed to lapse for economic reasons and/or unrest.

According to the CDC in the USA, as of 1 Dec 2018, 292 individual cases of measles have been confirmed in 26 states and the District of Columbia. This is the 2nd-highest number of cases since 2010, with 2014 reporting 667 cases (see https://www.cdc.gov/measles/cases-outbreaks.html). - Mod.LK

